rComments: Lecture slots are more like question and answer period. He posts the lecture videos online but it's just him regurgitating the slides. Quizzes are insanely difficult not because of the material but because he makes you use some counter-intuitive outdated software (EZ Solve). Only like 5 people show up to lecture out of a class of 160.
He clearly loves reactor design, but is an awful lecturer. He is not proficient at explaining concepts or problems and tends to use a condescending tone.

He knows his material, but he's a very hard marker. I get my exam back and he takes off 14 marks for a small calculation mistake. His professors probably marked him just as hard because for a small mistake he just rips you apart. Who ever is taking his class, expect a low grade - unless you study hard.
